text: Atamkul () is a rural locality (a selo) in Tarkazinsky Selsoviet, Yermekeyevsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 104 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 47 km from Yermekeyevo, 4 km from Tarkazy. == References == Category:Rural localities in Yermekeyevsky District
title: Atamkul
